         <abstract>
            <p>In this note, we solve an open problem of Flajolet and Schott concerning the rate of convergence of the zeros of Lommel polynomials to the zeros of a Bessel function (considered as a function of the order). The average case analysis of dynamic data structures was the initial motivation for this investigation. The Maple program, whose results are reported at the end, illustrates that our result is quite good.</p>
          </abstract>
